{"type":"text","timestamp":1773351668747,"sessionID":"ses_31c036d39ffedecysjCoQobMfd","part":{"id":"prt_ce3fee6b0001fNoAfKL0kkn507","sessionID":"ses_31c036d39ffedecysjCoQobMfd","messageID":"msg_ce3fedf26001j7FoyJ3Uwrq2yS","type":"text","text":"Implementation is complete. Here's a summary of what was implemented:\n\n## Summary\n\n### `wombo abort <feature-id>` command\n\n**Files changed:**\n1. **`src/commands/abort.ts`** (new) — Core abort command handler that:\n   - Loads wave state and finds the target agent\n   - Validates the agent is in an abortable state (`running`, `installing`, `queued`, or `resolving_conflict`)\n   - Kills the tmux session via `killTmuxSession()` \n   - Kills the agent process by PID via `SIGTERM` (if still running)\n   - Updates wave state: marks agent as `failed` (default) or `queued` (with `--requeue`)\n   - When requeuing, resets all retry-related fields for a fresh start\n   - Supports `--output json` for structured output\n\n2. **`src/index.ts`** — CLI integration:\n   - Added `--requeue` flag to `CLIArgs` interface and parser\n   - Added `abort` to the command router with usage validation\n   - Updated help text and usage comments with abort command + examples\n   - Imported `cmdAbort` from the new module\n\n3. **`src/lib/schema.ts`** — Schema introspection:\n   - Registered `abort` command in `COMMAND_REGISTRY` with positional `feature-id` and `--requeue` flag\n   - Supports `wombo describe abort` for AI agent consumption\n\n### Constraints satisfied:\n- ✅ Kills tmux session cleanly\n- ✅ Updates wave state to reflect the abort\n- ✅ Supports `--requeue` flag to return feature to queued instead of failed\n- ✅ Supports `--output json`\n- ✅ Typecheck passes\n- ✅ Build passes","time":{"start":1773351668745,"end":1773351668745}}}
